# git-workflow-rebase-worktree-signing — History

## v1.0.0 (2026-05-18) — Merge of 11 skills

**Changed by:** Skill-merge swarm (Phase C Wave 2, M7 / #1774)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

Consolidated 11 git-workflow skills into a single canonical reference covering:
- Rebase conflict resolution and pre-commit hook exclusions
- Batch rebase with worktree isolation (one worktree per branch)
- Stale agent worktree branch cleanup and classification
- Worktree lifecycle: create, switch, sync, migrate, and cleanup
- Branch-state recovery (commits on local main, stale PRs)
- Cherry-pick decision procedure for rejected PRs
- Stash-pop conflict resolution under Safety Net constraints
- Submodule worktree permission retry pattern
- Worktree agent plan-mode avoidance
- Integration tests for worktree transformation scripts
- Preservation-biased audit methodology for cleanup

---

