## Superseded from git-cherry-pick-dependent-commit-becomes-noop-when-prerequisite-dropped

```yaml
name: git-cherry-pick-dependent-commit-becomes-noop-when-prerequisite-dropped
category: tooling
date: 2026-05-15
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-local
tags: [git, cherry-pick, rejected-pr, salvage, dependent-commits, dead-code, yagni, conflict-resolution]
```

Decision procedure: when salvaging commits from a rejected PR via cherry-pick, inspect
the actual diff (`git show <commit> -- <file>`), not the subject line. If every added
line references the dropped feature, the commit is feature-scoped and should also be
dropped. Verified on ProjectOdyssey PR #5382 → #5407 (2026-05-15).

---

## Superseded from git-commits-on-local-main-recovery

```yaml
name: git-commits-on-local-main-recovery
category: tooling
date: 2026-04-25
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-local
```

Recovery when commits accidentally land on local main: `git checkout -b feat/<desc>`
creates a new branch pointer at current HEAD, including all commits. Local main stays
diverged but is harmless. Verified: 6 automation pipeline commits rescued into
feat/automation-6-phase-pipeline; PR #302 opened in ProjectHephaestus.

