## Superseded from git-rebase-stacked-prs-worktree-isolation

```yaml
name: git-rebase-stacked-prs-worktree-isolation
category: tooling
date: 2026-05-17
version: "1.1.0"
verification: verified-ci
history: git-rebase-stacked-prs-worktree-isolation.history
tags: [git, rebase, worktree, pr-stack, parallelism, conflict-resolution]
```

Use git worktrees to rebase a stack of sibling PRs in parallel without cross-iteration
corruption. Always pass `origin/<branch> --detach`; never the bare local branch name.
Verify rebase with merge-base check AND content-check before force-pushing. Verified:
14 sibling branches rebased across 5 parallel agents in ~3 min (vs ~30 min sequential)
on ProjectCharybdis. v1.1.0 added stale local branch pitfall from Myrmidons 2026-05-17.

v1.1.0 history entry:
- Added stale local branch pitfall: `git worktree add /tmp/wt cleanup/c3-remove-reconciler`
  silently picked up a stale local tip; fix-up commit on origin was erased by force-push.
- Added Quick Reference callout: always `git fetch origin --prune` first, then `origin/<branch> --detach`.
- Added post-rebase content check: `git diff --name-status origin/<base>..HEAD`.

