## Superseded from git-stash-pop-conflict-semantic-merge

```yaml
name: git-stash-pop-conflict-semantic-merge
category: tooling
date: 2026-04-25
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-local
```

Resolve merge conflicts from `git stash pop` when Safety Net blocks both discard
(`git checkout --`) and delete (`git stash drop`). Evaluate each conflict hunk
independently — do not apply global "accept ours/theirs". Verified on ProjectHephaestus
`skills/learn/SKILL.md` stash conflict.

---

## Superseded from git-worktree-cleanup-preservation-audit

```yaml
name: git-worktree-cleanup-preservation-audit
category: tooling
date: 2026-04-25
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-local
tags: [git, worktree, cleanup, stash, branch, preservation, audit, squash-merge, cherry, patch-id]
```

Systematic 3-method audit: PR state → patch-ID (git cherry) → message match + tree diff.
`git cherry` always shows `+` for squash-merged branches — not conclusive. Uncommitted
worktree drift is not real WIP. Safety Net blocks stash drop and --force operations;
hand to user. Verified: ProjectHermes cleanup session 2026-04-25.

---

## Superseded from rebase-conflict-resolution-and-hook-exclusions

```yaml
name: rebase-conflict-resolution-and-hook-exclusions
category: tooling
date: 2026-03-19
version: "1.0.0"
```

Fix multiple blocked PRs sharing a root cause on main: create a root-cause fix PR first,
then rebase feature branches. Pre-commit hook scanners with `pass_filenames: false` must
have exclusions inside the Python script (not in hook `exclude:` config). Python regex
conflict resolution for blocked `git checkout --theirs`. Verified: ProjectScylla.

