## Superseded from rebasing-stale-agent-worktree-branches

```yaml
name: rebasing-stale-agent-worktree-branches
category: tooling
date: 2026-05-03
version: "1.2.0"
verification: verified-local
history: rebasing-stale-agent-worktree-branches.history
tags: [git, rebase, worktree, agent, stale, cleanup, -X-ours, residual-diff, sub-agent, squash-merge, cherry, pre-flight, orphan, conflict-markers, union-merge, history-file]
```

Classify branches before rebasing (pre-flight gate). "ahead 1, behind N" is the
squash-merge artifact, not evidence of unmerged work. Use `git rebase -X ours` for
uniform reword conflicts; hash-compare residual diffs to cluster duplicates. Cherry=1
no-PR branches: check file existence on main before deleting. Orphaned conflict markers
in committed files: both halves may contain real content. v1.2.0 (2026-05-03): added
file-existence decision tree, orphaned marker scan, per-branch worktree for manual
resolution. Verified: ProjectMnemosyne sessions 2026-04-25 and 2026-05-03.

